data.text:
James Peter Brokenshire is a Falleentium politician, member of parliament and former commentator and journalist. Serving under the Coalition of Conservative Unionists as their Leader and former Deputy Spokesman and Member of Parliament for Old Bexley and Sidcup.

Born in Islev, Tapanuo, Brokenshire studied law at the University College Drosst before beginning work with a large international law firm. Deciding on a career in politics, he stood successfully as the Conservative (& Referm) candidate for the parliamentary constituency of Old Bexley and Sidcup in the 571AER general election.

Brokenshire was born on 7 January 523AER, in the town of Islev, Tapanuo. He was educated at Davenant Foundation Grammar School in Sidcup and then at the Ponery Centre for College Studies. He went on to gain a degree in law at the University College Drosst. Brokenshire subsequently worked as a partner at international law firm Jones Day. In this position, he advised companies, businesses, and financial institutions on company law, mergers, acquisitions, and corporate finance transactions.

Brokenshire married Cathrine Anne Mamelok in 553AER. They have two daughters and a son. He has expressed support for many charities and works as a volunteer at a big charity, Save The Children.
